<div class="container">
  <h1>MemoryMapCache & LayeredStore</h1>
  <p style="text-align: center; color: #a0aab2; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    Blazing fast, natively distributed inter-process caching for Ruby on Rails.
  </p>

  <div class="glass-panel" style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;">
    <div>
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">See it in Action</h2>
      <p style="margin: 0; color: #a0aab2; max-width: 600px;">
        Head over to our <b>Live Sandbox Demonstration</b> to actively force multi-threaded fragment generation and trace native cache miss latency. 
      </p>
    </div>
    <%= link_to "Launch Interactive Playground →", simulate_path, class: "btn active" %>
  </div>

  <div class="glass-panel">
    <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Installation</h2>
    <p>Getting started natively is simple. Install the rubygem from our releases:</p>
    <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; font-family: monospace;">
      gem "memory_map_cache"
    </div>
    <br/>
    <p>And easily inject it straight into your standard `config/environments/production.rb` configuration natively using ActiveSupport compliance mappings:</p>
    <div style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; font-family: monospace;">
      config.cache_store = :memory_map_cache_store, '/tmp/cache.bin'
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="glass-panel">
    <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Natively Fast. Easily Integratable.</h2>
    <p>We built this cache layer targeting aggressive optimization. The MemoryMapCache natively utilizes C-level `mmap` rendering out thousands of concurrent local Ruby hits in less than 32ms.</p>
    
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Cache Strategy</th>
          <th>Architecture Bounds</th>
          <th>Read Operations / sec</th>
          <th>Speed Improvement (Mixed Profile)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Redis Store</td>
          <td>Network InterProcess Socket</td>
          <td>~ 18,041 ops/sec</td>
          <td>Baseline (1x)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Memcached</td>
          <td>Network Distributed Daemon</td>
          <td>~ 51,619 ops/sec</td>
          <td>+2.86x Faster</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Litecache (SQLite)</td>
          <td>Local Database Engine</td>
          <td>~ 129,711 ops/sec</td>
          <td>+7.18x Faster</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>MemoryMapCache</strong></td>
          <td>Native Distributed Thread RAM</td>
          <td><strong>~ 150,240 ops/sec</strong></td>
          <td><strong>+8.32x Faster</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>LayeredStore (L1/L2)</strong></td>
          <td>Proxy Hydration Bridge</td>
          <td><strong>~ 148,805 ops/sec</strong></td>
          <td><strong>+8.24x Faster</strong></td>
        </tr>
    <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #ff8a00;">Concurrent Write Workload (4KB Payloads)</h3>
